The Spring 2019 White House Internship Program is now accepting applications until August 24, 2018. The program runs from January 16 to April 12, 2019, and applicants must be at least 18 years old, U.S. citizens, and able to commit to the full term. Eligible candidates include those currently enrolled in or graduated from an undergraduate or graduate degree program, as well as veterans who have served on active duty within the two years prior to the start date. Applicants are selected based on their commitment to public service, leadership, and support for the Trump Administration. More information and frequently asked questions can be found on the White House website.